article.description: Frankie Johnson stole the ball with six seconds left and then the freshman made two free throws as The Citadel held off VMI 79-74 on Saturday.
article.headline: Late steal, FTs and The Citadel holds off VMI 79-74 in SoCon
article.linkText: Late steal, FTs and The Citadel holds off VMI 79-74 in SoCon
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Frankie Johnson stole the ball with six seconds left and then the freshman made two free throws as The Citadel held off VMI 79-74 on Saturday. VMI's top scorer, QJ Peterson pulled the Keydets to 73-71 with just under three minutes remaining but missed two jump shots in the final minute and had just grabbed a defensive rebound when Johnson stripped the ball away with six seconds left. Peterson fouled, and Johnson made both free throws for a 79-74 lead and the Bulldogs held on as VMI missed two shots in the final two seconds. Johnson finished with nine points and was 3-for-4 at the foul line. Zane Najdawi led The Citadel (9-9, 2/3 Southern) with 25 points -- his eighth game this season with 20 or better -- and freshman Leandro Allende added a season-high 21. Peterson led the Keydets (3-11, 0-3) with 22 points and 12 boards, his second double-double.
